
1) What is a Java package?

packages are groups of related class

2) What is the CLASSPATH variable all about?


a variable that allows you to specify the path to all of the java classes in a particular package


3) What does the package structure mirror?

the relationship between a parent class and its subsaquint subclass

4.) How do packages affect access to Java classes?

the visible element is determined by its access specification and the package in which it resides


5.) What is an interface?

an interface species what must be done with and empty method

6) What makes interfaces unique?

they allow you to specify what must be done without telling you how to do it

7) What keyword is used to specify that a class is going to use a separate interface?

interface

8) What makes interfaces so useful?

one interface multiple methods- polymorphism

9) What was added in JDK 8 that makes interfaces even more useful?


it is now possible for an interface to specify some behavior


10) How many interfaces can a single class implement?

any number of interfaces